\title{Size of the rule set}

\p{While tbe number of rules in a type system is not a strict measure of its complexity,
it can be an effective heuristic for comparing two system in an inclusion relationship,
e.g., when system #{S_1} is a strict subset of system #{S_2}. In such cases, one can
reasonably claim that #{S_1} is simpler than #{S_2}, because it has fewer rules. Smaller
systems tend to be easier to work with.}
